# Env
# `.env` is whitelisted (with `!.env` overriding the root .gitignore's
# blanket `.env` rule) because it carries empty PUBLIC_* placeholders
# only — they're required at type-check time so SvelteKit can resolve
# `$env/static/public` imports without a populated build environment.
# Real values come from `--build-arg PUBLIC_SITE_URL=...` during Docker
# build, or from `.env.local` (gitignored) for local development.
# NEVER add secrets to `.env` — only PUBLIC_* placeholders.
!.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.test
.env.local

# Vite
vite.config.js.timestamp-*
vite.config.ts.timestamp-*
